# 🧬 Parasite Vision AI

An AI-powered image classification system that detects and classifies different parasite types from microscopic images using deep learning (PyTorch) and a web interface built with Streamlit.

---

## 🚀 Project Overview

Parasite Vision AI is a machine learning project designed to help identify common parasitic organisms from images.  
The model is trained using a convolutional neural network (**ResNet18**) and can predict the parasite type along with a confidence score.

### System Includes:
- 🧠 Deep learning model (ResNet18)
- 📸 Image classification pipeline
- 🌐 Web app interface using Streamlit
- 📊 Confidence score prediction
- 🔮 Real-time image testing

---

## 🦠 Supported Parasites

The model can classify:
- Ascaris egg  
- Hookworm egg  
- Trichuris egg  
- Taenia saginata egg  
- Schistosoma mansoni egg  
- Giardia lamblia cyst  
- Entamoeba histolytica egg  
- Plasmodium species (Malaria)

---

## 📂 Project Structure
ParasiteVisionAI/
│── data/              # Raw and processed images
│── notebooks/         # Training and evaluation notebooks
│── app.py             # Streamlit web interface
│── models/            # Saved model weights
│── requirements.txt   # Dependencies
│── README.md          # Project documentation

---

## ⚙️ Installation
```bash
git clone https://github.com/yourusername/ParasiteVisionAI.git
cd ParasiteVisionAI
pip install -r requirements.txt
▶️ Usage
Place parasite images in the data/ folder.

Run preprocessing scripts to prepare datasets.

Train and evaluate models in notebooks/.

Launch the Streamlit app:

bash
streamlit run app.py
📊 Example Output
Input: Microscopic image of parasite egg

Output: Predicted parasite type + confidence score
